developer, expects revenue to rise by at least 40 percent to 28
billion baht ($880 million) this year, President Srettha Thavisin said. The stock climbed.  Sansiri plans to develop more condominium projects in
provinces outside Bangkok, Srettha said in an e-mailed statement
today. The company has secured about 15 billion baht of bookings
for its residential projects, he said.  The companyâ€™s  shares (SIRI)  jumped 6.8 percent to 1.42 baht at the
